					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-655428#post-1791941</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-655428/scp-1846#post-1791941</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 07 Jun 2013 18:24:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>wishun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1204404</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>TL333s beat me to it. Scenes From A Multiverse was the very first thing that leap to my mind.</p> <p>I love the contempt this emmisary has for his deity and host-mates. He serves Srqnabotf, because that is an angel's nature, but he doesn't respect Him at all.</p> <p>I wonder if Srqnabotf is actually the one and only deity. Setting aside the possibility that the holy lobbyist is lieing; it seems to me that an angel of any deity would be predisposed to consider their patron to be the sole penultimate. Perhaps even fundamentally incapable of recognizing any other gods that may or may not exist in the pantheon.</p> <p>It also strikes me that 1846 might be telling just 90% of the truth, in order to better accomplish his task. Convincing the O5s that preventing corn-mageddon requires a cetain tonnage of crop every year seems a lot more likely to produce action than indirectly tweaking market prices via capitol hill. Less work, too. Instead of wining and dining and bribing dozens of congressmen, he just has to straight-talk a scientist or two and whistle up a bit of minor weather manipulation.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
