					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-655428#post-1782641</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-655428/scp-1846#post-1782641</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 24 May 2013 16:24:23 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Communism will win</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>617958</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Ah, realized what the inspiration was.</p> <p>Remember that bad Lucifer/angel knockoff that was posted a while back? I commented on its lack of imagination and gave a few ideas for what they COULD have done. People commented that one of the ideas, about an automated angel using an abacus to decide where to send people, was interesting, and I said I'd write it.</p> <p>I figured it would be more interesting if the angel were intelligent and hated his job. I also thought it would be funny for whether you're damned or not to be a function of something really stupid; say, how much corn you ate. And things sort of developed from there.</p> <p>An early draft gave him telepathic influence over people, and I thank someone in staff chat (maybe Djoric) for telling me to take it out.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
